NA, not a rip-and-replace.", "threat_level": "medium"}, {"date": "2026-05-20", "name": "Internal transformation assessment (unnamed partner)", "quote": "we have already started an assessment, but that's from... we have a specific partner on that", "source": "Avoma discovery call 20 May 2026 (Jathniel Ibanes)", "status": "active", "sentiment": "neutral", "how_we_win": "Insert Zycus into the roadmap work now so the assessment recommends a best-of-breed S2P platform rather than defaulting to ERP-only.", "threat_level": "low"}, {"date": "2024-03-18", "name": "Unknown vendors under evaluation (unconfirmed)", "quote": "they were looking into other vendors as well, but was not aware of it in detail", "source": "SF Next_Step__c 18 Mar 2024 (Ivan Alcatara)", "status": "faded", "sentiment": "neutral", "how_we_win": "No named rival; keep discovery open to surface any shortlist before an RFP forms.", "threat_level": "dormant"}]}, "champion_strength": {"source": "SF OpportunityContactRole (no Champion marked); SF Next_Step__c 26 May 2026; Avoma call 20 May 2026", "at_risk": true, "summary": "No confirmed champion. Jathniel Ibanes is engaged and owns the roadmap but is explicitly too junior to drive the deal, and there is no CPO above him. Joannie Festejo showed early willingness to escalate to Vicky Yap without confirmed follow-through. What has developed: a genuine working contact (Jath) and, newly, direct interest from the Decision Maker (Vicky) via Horizon. What is missing: a power-level advocate who will carry Zycus to the Digital Transformation Office approvers.", "champion": "Jathniel Ibanes (developing, too junior)", "strength": "weak"}, "stakeholder_map": {"items": [{"name": "Vicky Yap", "risk": "Budget-relevant procurement leader and closest thing to an economic buyer (no CPO exists); engaged for the first time via Horizon but not yet in a deal conversation. Losing this newly-opened thread would stall the deal.", "role": "Decision Maker", "email": "vicky.yap@urc.com.ph"